01:25:46.065 --> 01:25:48.424
How did you know about that?
I didn't tell you that.

01:25:48.425 --> 01:25:50.584
- You must have done.
- I really didn't.

01:25:50.585 --> 01:25:53.304
Well, maybe Sherlock told me.

01:25:53.305 --> 01:25:57.304
But you've met Sherlock
exactly once, in this room,

01:25:57.305 --> 01:25:58.624
he was off his head.

01:25:58.625 --> 01:26:01.544
Oh, no, no, I met him before that.

01:26:01.545 --> 01:26:02.864
When?

01:26:02.865 --> 01:26:06.784
We spent a night together. It was lovely.

01:26:06.785 --> 01:26:08.585
We had chips.

01:26:14.425 --> 01:26:17.265
"You're not what I expected, Mr Holmes."

01:26:18.345 --> 01:26:22.048
"You're... nicer."

01:26:33.665 --> 01:26:36.944
Culverton gave me Faith's original note.

01:26:36.945 --> 01:26:39.622
A mutual friend put us in touch.

01:26:40.505 --> 01:26:43.904
Did Sherlock ever
tell you about the note?

01:26:43.905 --> 01:26:46.584
I added some deductions for Sherlock.

01:26:46.585 --> 01:26:49.043
He was quite good.

01:26:50.225 --> 01:26:53.730
But... he didn't get the big one.

01:26:56.560 --> 01:26:59.816
_

01:27:05.705 --> 01:27:10.064
In fairness, though, he does
have excellent taste in chips.

01:27:10.065 --> 01:27:11.624
- What's that?
- What's what?

01:27:11.625 --> 01:27:13.624
The flower in your hair,
it's like I had on the bus.

01:27:13.625 --> 01:27:16.224
You looked very sweet.

01:27:16.225 --> 01:27:17.465
But then...

01:27:20.105 --> 01:27:22.904
"You have such nice eyes."

01:27:22.905 --> 01:27:26.224
Amazing the times a man doesn't
really look at your face.

01:27:26.225 --> 01:27:30.664
Oh, you can hide behind a
sexy smile or a walking cane,

01:27:30.665 --> 01:27:32.784
or just be a therapist,

01:27:32.785 --> 01:27:37.304
talking about you... all the time.

01:27:37.305 --> 01:27:38.824
Oh, please don't go anywhere,

01:27:38.825 --> 01:27:40.824
I'm sure the therapist
who actually lives here

01:27:40.825 --> 01:27:42.344
wouldn't want blood on the carpet.

01:27:42.345 --> 01:27:44.384
Oh, hang on, it's fine.

01:27:44.385 --> 01:27:46.144
She's in a sack in the airing cupboard.

01:27:46.145 --> 01:27:48.345
- Who are you?
- Isn't it obvious?

01:27:50.825 --> 01:27:52.544
Haven't you guessed?

01:27:52.545 --> 01:27:53.944
I'm Eurus.

01:27:53.945 --> 01:27:55.384
Eurus?

01:27:55.385 --> 01:27:59.984
Silly name, isn't it? Greek.
Means "the east wind".

01:27:59.985 --> 01:28:02.224
My parents loved silly names,

01:28:02.225 --> 01:28:04.744
like Eurus...

01:28:04.745 --> 01:28:06.984
or Mycroft...

01:28:06.985 --> 01:28:09.031
or Sherlock.

01:28:09.056 --> 01:28:10.824
Oh, look at him.

01:28:10.825 --> 01:28:12.984
Didn't it ever occur
to you, not even once,

01:28:12.985 --> 01:28:17.065
that Sherlock's secret brother might
just be Sherlock's secret sister?

01:28:18.745 --> 01:28:19.945
Huh?

01:28:21.065 --> 01:28:22.985
He's making a funny face.

01:28:25.065 --> 01:28:26.665
I think I'll put a hole in it.

